  "_comment": [
    "Candidate monomers the discovery pipeline checks each run, one PubChem lookup per entry.",
    "Add to this list to steer what gets discovered - the pipeline only ever considers names here,",
    "it does not crawl PubChem on its own. `monomer` must be a name PubChem's PUG REST /compound/name",
    "endpoint resolves to a real compound (test at https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/rest/pug/compound/name/<name>/property/CanonicalSMILES/JSON).",
    "`cls`/`tags`/`polymerName`/`aka` are supplied by hand (a human judgment call, not derived from PubChem)",
    "so the resulting DB entry reads the way the rest of the curated library does.",
    "Step-growth/condensation polymers (nylons, most polyesters) are intentionally NOT listed here:",
    "they need a monomer *pair* plus specific linkage chemistry that a single PubChem lookup can't supply,",
    "and PubChem generally has no compound record for the polymer name itself to fall back on either.",
    "Those stay a manual-entry workflow using the existing structure editor."
  ],
